# Setting

## Original setting (deprecated)

The lab and experiments were in an isolated, rural location — a pure secret lab setup. This felt boring and visually stale, like an isolated retreat with no opportunity for interaction with outside characters. We were stuck with just the main 4 characters. (human)

## New setting: Urban / Industrial

Instead of isolation, the setting is now urban — "hiding under everyone's noses." This allows characters to come and go more often; each character still spends half their time dealing with their own lives outside the lab. (human)

The machine needs a lot of energy. The team taps into a nearby electrical plant, using excess power that would otherwise be wasted. The setting becomes industrial — characters interact with other engineers and plant workers, hiding in plain sight. (human)

A potential 5th ancillary character: a worker at the power plant who gets read into the secrets of the machine. This person ends up helping the scientific team significantly, providing cover and assistance. (human)

The setting is specifically a coal plant. A dirty, dank, horrible location for a lab is a funny juxtaposition against their cutting-edge physics work. (human)

The coal plant is at risk of being shut down by the state. It's struggling, and everything at the plant is cutting corners. (human)

Scene idea: The characters have to scramble to justify to an uneducated boss of the power plant what results they're producing. They say "cancer research" in passing, and the boss latches onto it. Behind the scenes, the boss really runs with it, making it a huge PR point for the plant — that this coal plant "saves lives." This brings, in a funny way, way too much attention to the lab team. They have to keep lying about fake medical/cancer results. (human)

