## Machine teleports matter

The team only has enough money to run the experiment once — it will be a destructive test. The machine will not survive. (human)

The teleport occurs on the first experiment. In an earlier version of this script there was a long series of failed attempts before the first teleport; in this version the teleport happens on the very first run. (human)

First experiment scene: The machine runs, makes noise, and destructs. Three of the scientists are busy watching readouts and data. The fourth scientist, the one positioned to directly observe the machine's output, is left shocked and speechless — they are the only one who witnesses the teleport happen live. We only see that scientist's stunned reaction; we do not see the teleport itself on screen. Afterwards the team reviews film footage, and the teleport is revealed to the audience through the footage. (human)

The team accidentally teleports a chunk of molten magma. (human)

